09/12/2002
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The joint Croatian-Slovenian commission for economic co-operation starts its sixth round of negotiations in the Slovenian lake resort of Bled on Monday (9 December).
According to the Croatian Economy Ministry, the talks will focus on trade and investment issues.
A separate joint commission will meet Tuesday to evaluate implementation of the bilateral free trade agreement.
Slovenia is Croatia's third largest trade partner and the seventh largest foreign investor.
(Vjesnik - 09/12/02;
HINA - 08/12/02)
